== Roasted Carrots ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @carrots{2}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Roughly chop the @dill{1/2%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Roughly chop the @dried cranberries{30%g}.

> If you'd prefer to pan-fry your carrots, skip the oven and cut them into 1cm thick rounds instead.

Pop the carrots onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

To pan-fry your carrots, stir-fry in a large #frying pan{} until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Use the pan for the beef in step 4.

== Herby Bulgur ==

While the carrots roast, pour the @water for the bulgur{240%ml} into a #saucepan{}, stir in half the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat.

Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Chermoula Beef ==

Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Lower the heat to medium and add the @onion{1}(diced from before). Cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @Chermoula spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) into the beef. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @water for the beef{150%ml}, remaining chicken stock paste and dried cranberries. Stir together and bring to a gentle simmer.

Cook until the mixture has thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} with half the dill. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, fluff up the bulgur wheat with a #fork{} and stir through the remaining dill.

Share the herby bulgur between your #bowls{}, then top with the chermoula beef and roasted carrots.

Finish with a spoonful of dill yoghurt. Enjoy!